=== 2009年流感疫情 ===
[[File:H1N1_influenza_virus.jpg|thumb]]]]

{{See|2009年H1N1流感大流行}}

2009年4月26日，<ref name="h1n1">{{Cite web |title=Implementation of the International Health Regulations (2005), Report of the Review Committee on the Functioning of the International Health Regulations (2005) in relation to Pandemic (H1N1) 2009 |url=http://apps.who.int/gb/ebwha/pdf_files/WHA64/A64_10-en.pdf |accessdate=2020-01-31 |publisher=世界卫生组织 |archive-date=2015-05-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150514145306/http://apps.who.int/gb/ebwha/pdf_files/WHA64/A64_10-en.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>距离首次案例出现一个月，<ref name="Hoffman" />世界卫生组织即在[[2009年H1N1流感大流行|H1N1流感（猪流感）]]处于{{Link-en|流行大流感|Influenza pandemic|第三阶段}}时便首次宣布了“国际关注的突发公共卫生事件”。<ref name="Dopplick" /><ref>{{Cite web |title=猪流感 |url=https://www.who.int/mediacentre/news/statements/2009/h1n1_20090425/zh/ |accessdate=2020-01-31 |publisher=世界卫生组织 |author1=陈冯富珍 |archive-date=2020-09-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200925085624/https://www.who.int/mediacentre/news/statements/2009/h1n1_20090425/zh/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=美国和墨西哥的猪流感病–最新简报2 |url=https://www.who.int/csr/don/2009_04_26/zh/ |accessdate=2020-01-31 |publisher=世界卫生组织 |archive-date=2020-09-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200926164046/https://www.who.int/csr/don/2009_04_26/zh/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>在同一天，世界卫生组织官网在三小时内收到近200万次访问，迫使大型流行疾病需要自己的专门的官方网站予以介绍。<ref name="h1n1" />在宣布H1N1为国际关注的突发公共卫生事件时，该流感仅在三个国家被发现。<ref name="Hoffman" />因此宣布H1N1为国际关注的突发公共卫生事件加剧了公众的恐惧。<ref name="Gostin" />但是，根据2013年一项由世界卫生组织赞助的调查结果显示，尽管H1N1流感与季节性流感有很大的相似程度，可由于H1N1流感导致大量65岁以下人士的死亡，因此导致了更多的生命年损失。<ref>{{Cite journal |title=Global Mortality Estimates for the 2009 Influenza Pandemic from the GLaMOR Project: A Modeling Study |url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3841239/ |date=2013-11 |journal=公共科学图书馆：医学 |accessdate=2020-01-31 |issue=11 |doi=10.1371/journal.pmed.1001558 |volume=10 |page=e1001558 |pmid=24302890 |last3=Roger Lustig |last4=Robert J. Taylor |last5=Douglas M. Fleming |last6=Madelon Kroneman |last7=Maria D. Van Kerkhove |last8=Anthony W. Mounts |last9=W. John Paget |author1=Lone Simonsen |author2=Peter Spreeuwenberg |coauthors=the GLaMOR Collaborating Teams |archive-date=2021-01-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210106202248/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3841239/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

=== 2014年脊髓灰质炎疫情 ===
第二起“国际关注的突发公共卫生事件”是针对[[根除脊髓灰质炎计划|2014年脊髓灰质炎疫情]]，于2014年5月发布。由于这是[[脊髓灰质炎|脊髓灰质炎]]在[[脊髓灰質炎|野生脊灰病毒]]几近根除后的复活，因此被认为是“非常事件”。<ref>{{Cite web |title=世卫组织就《国际卫生条例》突发事件委员会关于野生脊灰病毒国际传播问题会议发表的声明 |url=https://www.who.int/mediacentre/news/statements/2014/polio-20140505/zh/ |accessdate=2020-01-31 |publisher=世界卫生组织 |archive-date=2020-09-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200927225413/https://www.who.int/mediacentre/news/statements/2014/polio-20140505/zh/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Global emergency declared as polio cases surge |url=https://www.newscientist.com/article/dn25518-global-emergency-declared-as-polio-cases-surge/ |accessdate=2020-01-31 |publisher=New Scientist |author1=Debora MacKenzie |archive-date=2021-01-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210111063225/https://www.newscientist.com/article/dn25518-global-emergency-declared-as-polio-cases-surge/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

基于[[阿富汗|阿富汗]]、[[巴基斯坦|巴基斯坦]]、[[尼日利亚|尼日利亚]]等地的少数病例，全球根治脊灰被认为有一定风险。<ref name="Gostin" />

2019年10月，巴基斯坦与阿富汗继续出现野生脊灰病毒导致的脊髓灰质炎病例。除了非洲和亚洲部分地区的新疫苗衍生病例外，其余病例都得到了审查，依旧保持为“国际关注的突发公共卫生事件”。<ref>{{Cite web |title=News Scan for Oct 04, 2019 |url=http://www.cidrap.umn.edu/news-perspective/2019/10/news-scan-oct-04-2019 |accessdate=2020-01-31 |publisher=Center for Infectious Disease Research and Policy |archive-date=2019-10-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191010090850/http://www.cidrap.umn.edu/news-perspective/2019/10/news-scan-oct-04-2019 |dead-url=no }}</ref>该期限在2019年12月11日被再次延长。<ref>{{Cite web |title=POLIO: PUBLIC HEALTH EMERGENCY OF INTERNATIONAL CONCERN |url=https://travelhealthpro.org.uk/news/483/polio-public-health-emergency-of-international-concern |accessdate=2020-01-31 |publisher=National Travel Health Network and Centre |archive-date=2020-01-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200112121223/https://travelhealthpro.org.uk/news/483/polio-public-health-emergency-of-international-concern |dead-url=yes }}</ref>

=== 2014年西非埃博拉疫情 ===
[[File:Ebola_Virus_TEM_PHIL_1832_lores.jpg|thumb]]]]

{{see|西非伊波拉病毒疫症}}

2014年3月，[[几内亚|几内亚]]和[[利比里亚|利比里亚]]宣布确诊了[[埃博拉出血热|埃博拉出血热]]；2014年5月，[[塞拉利昂|塞拉利昂]]也确诊了埃博拉出血热。2014年8月8日星期五，[[美国|美国]]和[[欧洲|欧洲]]也发现了数例埃博拉出血热病例。由于美欧出现埃博拉病例并早在非洲三国已进行了数月的密集传播之后，<ref name="Rull" />世界卫生组终于第三次宣布了“国际关注的突发公共卫生事件”以应对这次的[[西非埃博拉病毒疫情|西非埃博拉病毒疫情]]。<ref>{{Cite web |title=Ebola outbreak in West Africa declared a public health emergency of international concern |url=http://www.euro.who.int/en/health-topics/emergencies/pages/news/news/2014/08/ebola-outbreak-in-west-africa-declared-a-public-health-emergency-of-international-concern |accessdate=2020-01-31 |publisher=世界卫生组织 |archive-date=2019-06-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190603170416/http://www.euro.who.int/en/health-topics/emergencies/pages/news/news/2014/08/ebola-outbreak-in-west-africa-declared-a-public-health-emergency-of-international-concern |dead-url=yes }}</ref>

后来，一项评论表明，这种流行病对美国的影响导致了世界卫生组织对该疫情的关注升级。<ref name="Hoffman" />这是国际资源匮乏地区的第一个“国际关注的突发公共卫生事件”。<ref name="Rull" />

=== 2016年寨卡疫情 ===
[[File:Zika_EM_CDC_280116.tiff|thumb]]]]

{{see|寨卡病毒疫情 (2015-2016年)}}

2016年2月1日，世界卫生组织第四次宣布了“国际关注的突发公共卫生事件”，以应对[[美洲|美洲地区]]出现的[[小头畸形|小头畸形]]和[[格林－巴利综合征|格林－巴利综合征]]疫情。当时怀疑这次疫情与正在进行的[[寨卡病毒疫情_(2015-2016年)|2015年至2016年寨卡病毒疫情]]有关。<ref>{{Cite web |title=世卫组织总干事总结寨卡病毒突发事件委员会的会议结果 |url=https://www.who.int/zh/news-room/detail/01-02-2016-who-director-general-summarizes-the-outcome-of-the-emergency-committee-regarding-clusters-of-microcephaly-and-guillain-barr%C3%A9-syndrome |accessdate=2020-01-31 |publisher=世界卫生组织 |archive-date=2020-06-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200629195554/https://www.who.int/zh/news-room/detail/01-02-2016-who-director-general-summarizes-the-outcome-of-the-emergency-committee-regarding-clusters-of-microcephaly-and-guillain-barr%C3%A9-syndrome |dead-url=no }}</ref>后来的研究和证据消除了这些担忧。

2016年4月，世界卫生组织表示“科学界已认可将[[寨卡病毒|寨卡病毒]]为[[小头畸形|小头畸形]]和[[格林－巴利综合征|格林－巴利综合征]]的病因”。<ref>{{Cite web |title=Zika Virus Microcephaly And Guillain–Barré Syndrome Situation Report |url=https://apps.who.int/iris/bitstream/handle/10665/204961/zikasitrep_7Apr2016_eng.pdf |accessdate=2020-01-31 |publisher=世界卫生组织 |archive-date=2020-02-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200219191644/https://apps.who.int/iris/bitstream/handle/10665/204961/zikasitrep_7Apr2016_eng.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>这是首次针对[[蚊子傳播的疾病|蚊媒传染病]]的“国际关注的突发公共卫生事件”。<ref name="Gostin" />

2016年11月18日，世界卫生组织解除了针对该次疫情的“国际关注的突发公共卫生事件”。<ref>{{Cite web |title=《国际卫生条例（2005）》关于小头症、其它神经疾患和寨卡病毒问题突发事件委员会第五次会议 |url=https://www.who.int/zh/news-room/detail/18-11-2016-fifth-meeting-of-the-emergency-committee-under-the-international-health-regulations-(2005)-regarding-microcephaly-other-neurological-disorders-and-zika-virus |accessdate=2020-01-31 |publisher=世界卫生组织 |archive-date=2020-09-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200927071855/https://www.who.int/zh/news-room/detail/18-11-2016-fifth-meeting-of-the-emergency-committee-under-the-international-health-regulations-%282005%29-regarding-microcephaly-other-neurological-disorders-and-zika-virus |dead-url=no }}</ref>

=== 2018－2020年刚果埃博拉疫情 ===
{{see|2018年－2019年剛果基伍伊波拉出血熱爆發}}

在2018年10月和稍后的2019年4月，世界卫生组织两次拒绝宣布[[2018年－2019年剛果基伍伊波拉出血熱爆發|2018年至2019年刚果基伍埃博拉疫情]]为“国际关注的突发公共卫生事件”。<ref>{{Cite journal |title=DR Congo Ebola outbreak not given PHEIC designation |url=https://www.thelancet.com/journals/lancet/article/PIIS0140-6736(19)30893-1/fulltext |date=2019-04-20 |journal=[[柳叶刀|柳叶刀]] |accessdate=2020-01-31 |issue=10181 |doi=10.1016/S0140-6736(19)30893-1 |volume=393 |page=1586 |pmid=31007190 |author1=Andrew Green |archive-date=2020-09-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200927032636/https://www.thelancet.com/journals/lancet/article/PIIS0140-6736(19)30893-1/fulltext |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=就《国际卫生条例》突发事件委员会于2018年10月召开的刚果民主共和国埃博拉病毒病疫情会议发表的声明 |url=https://www.who.int/zh/news-room/detail/17-10-2018-statement-on-the-meeting-of-the-ihr-emergency-committee-on-the-ebola-outbreak-in-drc |accessdate=2020-01-31 |publisher=世界卫生组织 |archive-date=2020-09-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200924195425/https://www.who.int/zh/news-room/detail/17-10-2018-statement-on-the-meeting-of-the-ihr-emergency-committee-on-the-ebola-outbreak-in-drc |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=刚果民主共和国埃博拉病毒病问题《国际卫生条例（2005）》突发事件委员会2019年4月12日会议的声明 |url=https://www.who.int/zh/news-room/detail/12-04-2019-statement-on-the-meeting-of-the-international-health-regulations-(2005)-emergency-committee-for-ebola-virus-disease-in-the-democratic-republic-of-the-congo-on-12th-april-2019 |accessdate=2020-01-31 |publisher=世界卫生组织 |archive-date=2020-09-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200930075619/https://www.who.int/zh/news-room/detail/12-04-2019-statement-on-the-meeting-of-the-international-health-regulations-%282005%29-emergency-committee-for-ebola-virus-disease-in-the-democratic-republic-of-the-congo-on-12th-april-2019 |dead-url=no }}</ref>这项决议引发了争议，{{Link-en|传染病研究与政策中心|Center for Infectious Disease Research and Policy}}主任{{Link-en|迈克尔·奥斯特霍姆|Michael Osterholm}}对此表示失望，并声称这种情况是“[[刚果民主共和国|刚果民主共和国]]仿佛坐在[[埃博拉病毒|埃博拉病毒]]瓦斯上，正等着被火柴引爆”。<ref name="Cohen">{{Cite web |title=Ebola outbreak in Congo still not an international crisis, WHO decides |url=https://www.sciencemag.org/news/2019/04/ebola-outbreak-congo-still-not-international-crisis-who-decides |accessdate=2020-01-31 |publisher=[[美国科学促进会|美国科学促进会]] |author1=Jon Cohen |website=[[科学_(期刊)|科学]] |archive-date=2019-06-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190604053227/https://www.sciencemag.org/news/2019/04/ebola-outbreak-congo-still-not-international-crisis-who-decides |dead-url=no }}</ref>但是世卫组织专家一直认为宣布“国际关注的突发公共卫生事件”对疫情控制并无益处。<ref name="Cohen" />尽管世界卫生组织拒绝宣布“国际关注的突发公共卫生事件”的确符合相关标准，但是针对2018年10月和2019年4月两次声明的批评声浪还是引发了对《国际卫生条例》突发事件委员会透明性的质疑。声明中针对刚果基伍埃博拉疫情所使用的语言都是不同的。突发事件委员会在2018年10月的声明中表示“目前不应该宣布为国际关注的突发公共卫生事件”。但是在先前拒绝宣布“国际关注的突发公共卫生事件”的13项理由中，其结果声明却说“不满足国际关注的突发公共卫生事件的条件”和“不构成国际关注的突发公共卫生事件”。而在2019年4月的声明中又表示“在此阶段宣布为国际关注的突发公共卫生事件没有任何的好处”，但这个理由并不符合《[[国际卫生条例|国际卫生条例]]》所规定的国际关注的突发公共卫生事件标准。<ref name="Eccleston-Turner" /><ref>{{Cite journal |title=Acknowledging the limits of public health solutions |url=https://www.thelancet.com/journals/lancet/article/PIIS0140-6736(19)31183-3/fulltext |date=2019-05-25 |journal=[[柳叶刀|柳叶刀]] |accessdate=2020-01-31 |issue=10186 |doi=10.1016/S0140-6736(19)31183-3 |volume=393 |page=2100 |pmid=31226033 |author1=柳叶刀编辑部 |archive-date=2020-09-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200925092843/https://www.thelancet.com/journals/lancet/article/PIIS0140-6736(19)31183-3/fulltext |dead-url=no }}</ref>

在2019年6月于[[刚果民主共和国|刚果民主共和国]]邻国[[乌干达|乌干达]]也发现埃博拉病毒确诊病例之后，世界卫生组织总干事[[特沃德罗斯·阿达诺姆|特沃德罗斯·阿达诺姆]]宣布将于2019年6月14日举行专家组第三次会议，以评估此次疫情是否达到“国际关注的突发公共卫生事件”标准。<ref>{{Cite web |title=Ebola outbreak enters 'truly frightening phase' as it turns deadly in Uganda |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2019/06/12/health/ebola-outbreak-death-uganda-africa-intl-bn/index.html |accessdate=2020-01-31 |publisher=[[有线电视新闻网|有线电视新闻网]] |author1=Katie Hunt |author2=Brent Swails |archive-date=2019-06-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190612145211/https://edition.cnn.com/2019/06/12/health/ebola-outbreak-death-uganda-africa-intl-bn/index.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Boy, 5, and Grandmother Die in Uganda as More Ebola Cases Emerge |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/06/12/world/africa/ebola-uganda-congo.html |accessdate=2020-01-31 |publisher=[[纽约时报|纽约时报]] |author1=Rick Gladstone |archive-date=2019-06-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190617164217/https://www.nytimes.com/2019/06/12/world/africa/ebola-uganda-congo.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>但这次专家会议的结论却是，虽然此次疫情的爆发是刚果民主共和国乃至该国周边地区的紧急健康事件，但还是未满足“国际关注的突发公共卫生事件”的三个标准。<ref>{{Cite web |title=就刚果民主共和国埃博拉病毒病举行的《国际卫生条例(2005)》突发事件委员会会议的声明 |url=https://www.who.int/zh/news-room/detail/14-06-2019-statement-on-the-meeting-of-the-international-health-regulations-(2005)-emergency-committee-for-ebola-virus-disease-in-the-democratic-republic-of-the-congo |accessdate=2020-01-31 |publisher=世界卫生组织 |archive-date=2020-09-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200922072733/https://www.who.int/zh/news-room/detail/14-06-2019-statement-on-the-meeting-of-the-international-health-regulations-%282005%29-emergency-committee-for-ebola-virus-disease-in-the-democratic-republic-of-the-congo |dead-url=no }}</ref>尽管2019年6月11日，因埃博拉病毒死亡的人数达到1,405人；而到6月17日，死亡人数更是上升到1,440人，但是未宣布“国际关注的突发公共卫生事件”的理由在于此次疫情的国际传播力被认为影响较小，而宣布之后对刚果经济的损害风险较高。<ref>{{Cite web |title=Ebola case counts spike again in DRC |url=http://www.cidrap.umn.edu/news-perspective/2019/06/ebola-case-counts-spike-again-drc |accessdate=2020-01-31 |author=Stephanie Soucheray |publisher=Center for Infectious Disease Research and Policy |archive-date=2019-06-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190618223144/http://www.cidrap.umn.edu/news-perspective/2019/06/ebola-case-counts-spike-again-drc |dead-url=no }}</ref>[[特沃德罗斯·阿达诺姆|阿达诺姆]]认为宣布“国际关注的突发公共卫生事件”并不是为此次疫情筹措款项的正当方法。<ref>{{Cite web |title=WHO will take up Ebola emergency declaration question for a fourth time |url=http://www.cidrap.umn.edu/news-perspective/2019/07/who-will-take-ebola-emergency-declaration-question-fourth-time |accessdate=2020-01-31 |publisher=Center for Infectious Disease Research and Policy |author1=Stephanie Soucheray |archive-date=2019-07-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190717105305/http://www.cidrap.umn.edu/news-perspective/2019/07/who-will-take-ebola-emergency-declaration-question-fourth-time |dead-url=no }}</ref>

认识到[[埃博拉病毒|埃博拉病毒]]有极大的风险将扩散到[[刚果民主共和国|刚果民主共和国]][[北基伍省|北基伍省]]的首府[[戈马|戈马]]，{{Link-en|丹尼尔·鲁西|Daniel R. Lucey}}与[[罗恩·克莱恩|罗恩·克莱恩]]（美国前{{Link-en|埃博拉疫情在美国|Ebola virus cases in the United States|埃博拉疫情应对协调员}}）在《[[华盛顿邮报|华盛顿邮报]]》上发表文章呼吁尽快宣布“国际关注的突发公共卫生事件”。他们说：“如果疫情没有走在已经消灭的道路上，那么相反的情况，也就是疫情严重升级也是极有可能的。目前疫情有极高的风险逼近至刚果戈马，而戈马是一个拥有百万人口并建有国际机场的城市；甚至有可能跨越国境蔓延至[[南苏丹|南苏丹]]的难民营。由于剩余的疫苗剂量非常有限，上述任何一个情况的出现都将是一场灾难。”<ref>{{Cite web |title=Three more health workers infected in Ebola outbreak |url=http://www.cidrap.umn.edu/news-perspective/2019/07/three-more-health-workers-infected-ebola-outbreak |accessdate=2020-01-31 |publisher=Center for Infectious Disease Research and Policy |author1=Stephanie Soucheray |archive-date=2019-07-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190716072802/http://www.cidrap.umn.edu/news-perspective/2019/07/three-more-health-workers-infected-ebola-outbreak |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=It’s time to declare a public health emergency on Ebola |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/opinions/its-time-to-declare-a-public-health-emergency-on-ebola/2019/07/10/c77641fc-a327-11e9-b732-41a79c2551bf_story.html |accessdate=2020-01-31 |publisher=[[华盛顿邮报|华盛顿邮报]] |author1=Ronald A. Klain |author2=Daniel Lucey |archive-date=2019-07-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190716150837/https://www.washingtonpost.com/opinions/its-time-to-declare-a-public-health-emergency-on-ebola/2019/07/10/c77641fc-a327-11e9-b732-41a79c2551bf_story.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>四天后，也就是2019年7月14日，在拥有国际机场和高流动人口的[[戈马|戈马]]确诊了埃博拉病例。随后，世界卫生组织宣布将在2019年7月17日召开第四次突发事件委员会会议。当时，他们宣布该次疫情为“区域紧急状态，但绝不是全球威胁”；并同时宣布此次疫情为“国际关注的突发公共卫生事件”；同时不受贸易或旅行的限制。<ref>{{Cite web |title=刚果民主共和国埃博拉疫情被宣布为国际关注的突发公共卫生事件 |url=https://www.who.int/zh/news-room/detail/17-07-2019-ebola-outbreak-in-the-democratic-republic-of-the-congo-declared-a-public-health-emergency-of-international-concern |accessdate=2020-01-31 |publisher=世界卫生组织 |archive-date=2020-09-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200929163401/https://www.who.int/zh/news-room/detail/17-07-2019-ebola-outbreak-in-the-democratic-republic-of-the-congo-declared-a-public-health-emergency-of-international-concern |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=DR Congo Ebola outbreak declared global health emergency |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/health-49025298 |accessdate=2020-01-31 |publisher=[[英国广播公司|英国广播公司]] |website=[[BBC新闻|BBC新闻]] |archive-date=2019-07-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190717180532/https://www.bbc.com/news/health-49025298 |dead-url=no }}</ref>为响应该声明，刚果民主共和国总统与由病毒学家领导的专家组共同直接负责监督行动；而反对该声明的卫生部长{{Link-en|奥利·伊伦加·卡伦加|Oly Ilunga Kalenga}}则选择了辞职。<ref>{{Cite web |title=DRC health minister resigns after government takes Ebola reins |url=http://www.cidrap.umn.edu/news-perspective/2019/07/drc-health-minister-resigns-after-government-takes-ebola-reins |accessdate=2020-01-31 |publisher=Center for Infectious Disease Research and Policy |author1=Stephanie Soucheray |archive-date=2019-07-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190726060848/http://www.cidrap.umn.edu/news-perspective/2019/07/drc-health-minister-resigns-after-government-takes-ebola-reins |dead-url=no }}</ref>2019年10月10日，突发事件委员会将对本次疫情的控制情况进行第一次审查。<ref>{{Cite web |title=Response resumes following security problems in DRC Ebola hot spot |url=http://www.cidrap.umn.edu/news-perspective/2019/10/response-resumes-following-security-problems-drc-ebola-hot-spot |accessdate=2020-01-31 |publisher=Center for Infectious Disease Research and Policy |author1=Lisa Schnirring |archive-date=2019-10-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191010022043/http://www.cidrap.umn.edu/news-perspective/2019/10/response-resumes-following-security-problems-drc-ebola-hot-spot |dead-url=no }}</ref>截至2019年10月17日，该国际关注的突发公共卫生事件仍未解除。<ref>{{Cite web |title=2019年10月18日《国际卫生条例（2005）》突发事件委员会审查刚果民主共和国当前埃博拉病毒病疫情问题会议的声明 |url=https://www.who.int/zh/news-room/detail/18-10-2019-statement-on-the-meeting-of-the-international-health-regulations-(2005)-emergency-committee-for-ebola-virus-disease-in-the-democratic-republic-of-the-congo |accessdate=2020-01-31 |publisher=世界卫生组织 |archive-date=2020-09-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200928190437/https://www.who.int/zh/news-room/detail/18-10-2019-statement-on-the-meeting-of-the-international-health-regulations-%282005%29-emergency-committee-for-ebola-virus-disease-in-the-democratic-republic-of-the-congo |dead-url=no }}</ref>

