即使没有被正式宣布，国际关注的突发公共卫生事件也可以成为新闻，就如同[[2012年中東呼吸綜合症爆發|2012年至2013年中东呼吸综合症疫情]]一样。<ref>{{Cite web |title=MERS does not constitute a Public Health Emergency of International Concern (PHEIC): Emergency committee |url=http://www.theglobaldispatch.com/mers-does-not-constitute-a-public-health-emergency-of-international-concern-pheic-emergency-committee-32451/ |accessdate=2020-01-31 |publisher=The Global Dispatch Inc. |archive-date=2014-05-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140508062041/http://www.theglobaldispatch.com/mers-does-not-constitute-a-public-health-emergency-of-international-concern-pheic-emergency-committee-32451/ |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=WHO Statement: Second Meeting of the IHR Emergency Committee concerning MERS-CoV – PHEIC Conditions Not Met |url=https://centerforvaccineethicsandpolicy.net/2013/07/20/who-statement-second-meeting-of-the-ihr-emergency-committee-concerning-mers-cov-pheic-conditions-not-met/ |accessdate=2020-01-31 |publisher=VACCINES AND GLOBAL HEALTH :: ETHICS AND POLICY |archive-date=2016-04-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160406182541/http://centerforvaccineethicsandpolicy.net/2013/07/20/who-statement-second-meeting-of-the-ihr-emergency-committee-concerning-mers-cov-pheic-conditions-not-met/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>[[中东呼吸综合症|中东呼吸综合症]]原发于[[沙特阿拉伯|沙特阿拉伯]]，后扩散至24个国家或地区。截至2015年，中东呼吸综合症共计导致多达580余人死亡；而其中大多数病例是在医院内而并非持续的社区传播中。因此，究竟是什么构成了“国际关注的突发公共卫生事件”，目前尚不清楚。<ref name="Halabi" />

== 非传染事件 ==
国际关注的突发公共卫生事件不仅限于[[传染病|传染病]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hhs.gov/news/press/2009pres/03/20090325a.html|title=HHS Acting Secretary Declares Public Health Emergency for North Dakota Storms|date=2009-03-25|access-date=2021-05-22|archive-date=2013-12-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131227193228/http://www.hhs.gov/news/press/2009pres/03/20090325a.html}}</ref>
* the [[2009_swine_flu_pandemic|2009 swine flu pandemic]], which [[Homeland_Security|Homeland Security]] Secretary [[Janet_Napolitano|Janet Napolitano]] described as a "declaration of emergency preparedness."<ref name=AP426>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/aponline/2009/04/26/us/politics/AP-US-Swine-Flu-Emergency.html?_r=1|title=US Declares Public Health Emergency for Swine Flu|date=2009-04-26|publisher=Associated Press}} {{Dead link|date=September 2010|bot=RjwilmsiBot}}</ref>，而且可能也涵盖由化学制剂或放射性核材料引起的紧急情况。<ref name="Halabi" />[[抗生素耐药性|抗生素耐药性]]的出现和传播可能构成新的“国际关注的突发公共卫生事件”。<ref>{{Cite web |title=Can the International Health Regulations apply to antimicrobial resistance? |url=https://medicalxpress.com/news/2011-04-international-health-antimicrobial-resistance.html |accessdate=2020-01-30 |publisher=Public Library of Science |website=Medical X Press |archive-date=2020-01-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200122043710/https://medicalxpress.com/news/2011-04-international-health-antimicrobial-resistance.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal |title=A Call for Action: The Application of the International Health Regulations to the Global Threat of Antimicrobial Resistance |url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3079636/ |date=2011-04 |journal={{Link-en|公共科学图书馆：医学|PLOS Medicine}} |accessdate=2020-01-30 |issue=4 |doi=10.1371/journal.pmed.1001022 |volume=8 |pmid=21526227 |last3=John Conly |last4=Stephan Harbarth |last5=Yehuda Carmeli |last6=Ilona Kickbusch |author1=Didier Wernli |author2=Thomas Haustein |archive-date=2021-01-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210102183312/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3079636/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal |title=A Public Health Emergency of International Concern? Response to a Proposal to Apply the International Health Regulations to Antimicrobial Resistance |url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3080965/ |date=2011-04 |journal=公共科学图书馆：医学 |accessdate=2020-01-30 |is